args:
Ranzal regales the group with tales of a past
visit to Valkaheim, a city where anyone can
rise to new heights. According to him,
ambitious young people compete with
strangers and friends alike to climb
the proffered ladder of success.
Hey, old man! You fallin' asleep there?!
Bwa ha ha! This old man don't even need\na weaponâ€”not when I got my FISTS!
My right fist is The Hammer and my left is\nThe Anvilâ€”and yer gonna meet 'em both!\nNow let's get this punch party started!
Are you NUTS?! Use a weapon, dude!
Yeah, probably better let my trusty axe\nhave some fun. Hraaaagh!
...I've seen a lot of crazy things in my\ntime, Ranzal, but that was flat-out INSANE.
How the heck did you get so ripped?
Bwaaa ha ha! A mercenary who can't\nfight hand-to-hand ain't worth the coin\nwhat ya pay 'em with.
Only two things ya need in this world:\nA will to live and a hot meal.
I think I'm too soft and delicate to live\nthat kind of brutal existence.
Is there a way for me to get stronger\nthat doesn't involve so much...that?
Well yeah, I know another way.\nAin't sure it's EASIER, but...
Lemme tell ya about a little somethin'\nI learned when I visited a certain city\nback in the day...
So here's the thing about the\nfolks what live there...
(The hell's goin' on?! This guy's scrawny,\nbut his attacks are ridiculously strong!)
(I thought I'd finish this thing with a\ncouple'a blows, but now I'm fightin'\nfor my damn life!)
Ya got some serious skills, kid!\nWho taught ya to swing a sword?
I don't have time for lessons! ...Haaah!
But so long as I fight every day,\nI'll eventually become a knight!
Don't be daft! Only fancy nobles and\nthe like can enter the knighthood!
No matter how hard a street punk\nlike you works, they ain't never gonnaâ€”
Maybe that's the deal where you come\nfrom, but it's not the way of Valkaheim!
That's why I'm gonna take you down;\nI ain't losin' out on my dream now!
(Damn, look at his eyes... I don't think\nhe's been magicked, but he's clearly\ngone off his rocker!)
(The hell happened to make this guy\nso damn intense?!)
...I decided to leave town after that fight,\nbut on my way out, I happened to hear\nthe local lord givin' a speech.
That's when I suddenly realized why the\nkid had been fightin' so desperately.
Hear me, people of Valkaheim!\nI bestow upon you a dream!
A dream for all, regardless of rank or\nposition of birth! If you temper yourselves\nand train hard, you WILL become someone!

Cultivate your skill in the art of war!
Grow the seeds of your wisdom!
Come to understand strategy and do not
content yourselves with tranquility!
Battle your friends until one of you lies\nbloody and beaten, then forge new\nfriendships with those who survive!

Should you succeed, you will be promoted
to any station you choose. But should you
fail to become a person of measure,
you will have only death to comfort you.
This is the one law of Valkaheim, and the\ndream I bestow upon you as her prince!
Holy smokes. That guy's serious business!
Oh, you don't know the half of it.
That day, I learned that nothin' makes\na person stronger than a dream.

That's why I had such a hard time with
the crazy street punk what attacked me.
His dream gave him the mad strength
of a dozen fiends.
Man, I always thought of dreams\nas something...you know, happy?
Heh. There's all kinds'a dreams out there.\nSome of 'em smell all rosy and nice...

But the other kindâ€”the ones what make
me a little jealousâ€”light a white-hot fire
that makes a person willin' to lay 
absolutely everything on the line.
A city where that kinda dream is all ya\nget sounds like hell on earth to me.
But the folks who live there don't think so.\nThey chase it with everything they got,\nand it makes 'em stronger than anything.
